They are used to extract class, methods or field names during run time.
Get lists of names:
getDeclaredMethods
getClassName
getReturnType
getParameterTypes
getExceptions

Method invoke:
Now I have method name. Parameter types
Method meth = new Method();
meth.invoke(<className>, arguments);

Change field values:
Field f = class.getField(<filedname>); // Class<?> c
Use setInt, setBoolean etc to set primitive type values. Ex: f.setInt(student, 10) // student is the object of the class where field f exists.